macro.title: Do Chicago homes in white neighborhoods see higher private listing rates?
macro.what: Zillow finds 7.9% of homes in majority-white Chicago neighborhoods are listed privately, over twice the rate in non-white areas.
macro.why: Rates & inflation shape discount rates and housing affordability.
macro.market: Lower rates support demand/valuations; higher rates pressure builders/REITs and slow transactions.

macro.what: The September jobs report shows 119,000 jobs created but it's the slowest job growth in the 21st century outside a recession.
macro.why: Relevant development for housing and markets.
macro.market: Watch second-order effects across builders, lenders, and REITs.
